    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author `GetOrgTemplatesHandler` (NEW) at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/GetOrgTemplatesHandler.cs` implementing the T4 `get_org_templates(category?)` tool per architecture §8.1. READ-ONLY: reads org-level template entities from Dataverse via `IOrgTemplatesService` (architecture §4.4 — verify or create as a thin read-only service). Optional `category` filter. Returns `Array<{ templateId, name, type, content }>`. Implements FR-30 (get_org_templates row of the 8-tool surface).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat tool-handler authoring + Dataverse org-template entity read patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    `GetOrgTemplatesHandler` lives at `Services/Ai/Handlers/GetOrgTemplatesHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Reads via `IOrgTemplatesService` (existing if shared; else minimal new service). Optional `category` parameter filters results. Returns `Array<{ templateId, name, type, content }>` per §8.1. Graceful degradation on read failure: returns empty array + Warning log per §9.1. Single `ToolResult`; tier-1-safe telemetry; ≤+0.1 MB delta. Unit tests cover hit, category filter, empty result, defaults-on-failure, ADR-015 telemetry safety.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §3.1 (T4) + §4.4 (OrgTemplatesService — verify or create) + §8.1 schema + §8.2 routing (always-on). T4 is bound by ADR-013 facade; chat code READS via this handler; WRITES go through org-admin UI (out of scope here).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/ManagePinnedContextHandler.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No new endpoint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Auto-discovered; `IOrgTemplatesService` is registered by task 091.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">T4 reads via service abstraction; NO direct `IDataverseClient` injection into the handler.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry payload: handlerName + sessionId + tenantId + decision (`hit_<n>` | `empty` | `failure`) + durationMs ONLY. NEVER template names, content, or category strings.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">≤+0.1 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">SINGLE `ToolResult` return.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§3.2 rule 3 — T4 bound by ADR-013; chat reads only; writes via org-admin UI.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§9.1 — graceful degradation on read failure: empty array + Warning.</constraint>
  </constraints>

