  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load architecture §3.1, §4.4, §8.1, §9.1.</step>
    <step order="2">Grep across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` for `OrgTemplate` (and `sprk_template` if a Dataverse entity is established) to confirm presence; if absent, author `Services/Ai/Memory/IOrgTemplatesService.cs` + `OrgTemplatesService.cs` as minimal read-only wrapper. Confirm the actual Dataverse entity name (e.g., `sprk_orgtemplate`); if the entity does not yet exist, return an empty array (graceful) and document the gap in `notes/debug/090-org-templates-entity-gap.md` for follow-up.</step>
    <step order="3">Author `Services/Ai/Handlers/GetOrgTemplatesHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Parameter: `category` (optional).</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `ExecuteAsync`: call `IOrgTemplatesService.ListAsync(tenantId, category, ct)`; map results to `Array<{ templateId, name, type, content }>`; empty array on failure with Warning log per §9.1.</step>
    <step order="5">Add Dataverse seed-row JSON at `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-get-org-templates-row.json`.</step>
    <step order="6">Author unit tests: hit, category filter, empty result, defaults-on-failure, ADR-015 telemetry safety.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Measure BFF publish-size delta; write `notes/handoffs/090-bff-publish-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5).</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 090 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Reference handlers + architecture</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Locate existing OrgTemplatesService / sprk_orgtemplate</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Handler + (possibly) service + tests + seed-row JSON</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build / test / publish</tool>
  </tools>

